<refentry id="MGR-SWITCHOVERGTM">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>SWITCHOVER GTMCOOR</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>SWITCHOVER GTMCOOR</refname>
    <refpurpose>gtmcoor master, gtmcoor slave switchover, the original master changes to slave and the original slave changes to master</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="mgr-switchovergtm">
    <primary>SWITCHOVER GTMCOOR</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <synopsis>
SWITCHOVER GTMCOOR SLAVE <replaceable class="parameter">gtm_name</replaceable>
</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>
<command>SWITCHOVER GTMCOOR</command> gtmcoor master, gtmcoor slave switchover, the original master changes to slave and the original slave changes to master. These conditions must be satisfied before it is allowed to execute \"SWITCHOVER\" command: the master and slave have the same xlog position; there are not active connections on all coordinators and not conditions on all datanode masters.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Parameters</title>
  <variablelist>
    
   <varlistentry>
    <term><replaceable class="parameter">gtm_name</replaceable></term>
    <listitem>
      <para>
      Gtmcoor slave name.
      </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>

  </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  
  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>

    <para>
      Switchover gtmcoor slave, gtmcoor master:
<programlisting>
switchover gtmcoor slave gtm_name;
</programlisting>
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  
